description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experienced Social Worker, Assessment &amp; Review Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: £36,411 to £37,729 p.a.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Swindon Borough Council we have a clear vision of what we want the future to look like. The success of our vision depends on supporting residents to remain independent in their own homes with access to effective information and advice and services that promote a strength base approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have vacancies for registered Social Workers and Experienced Social Workers in the Assessment &amp; Review Team and would welcome applications from newly Qualified and Experienced Social Workers. Furthermore, we have a number of positons and a variety of hours available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team comprises of Social Workers and Occupational Therapists working together to provide a multi-disciplinary, strength-based approach to care management. We also work closely and collaboratively with our Live Well Hub, which utilises Community Navigators, volunteers and a wide range of community services, in order to ensure we work creatively with people to help them meet their desired outcomes. Come and meet us to see for yourself!’&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are interested in applicants who have experience of, and a passion to work with adults and are committed to providing a person centred and strengths based approach to their work. The successful candidates will join a friendly, supportive and dynamic team.  We provide good quality supervision and continuing professional development opportunities. We also believe that the success of our vision will depend on fostering our talent of the future and that is why we have these exciting new opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will get in return&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Benefit from corporate subscription to RiPFA including attendance at events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervision and support from onsite Leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wider training and support, including access to mentoring and an apprentice network.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;25 days holiday / a career average revalued earnings (CARE) pension scheme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eating Out, Shopping and Entertainment discounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To apply you will need&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you can bring good communication skills, teamwork and a passion to learn, we will support you in developing a career with Swindon Borough Council.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidates must be fluent in the English language (as a requirement of Part 7 of the Immigration Act for the effective performance of a customer-facing role).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Social Work England Registered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; For an informal discussion on the role please contact either Lee Aldridge, Team Manager on 07966 744260,laldridge@swindon.gov.uk or Chris Hogg, Assistant Team Manager on 07989 391225, chogg@swindon.gov.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 8 November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: w/c 16 November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
